<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFC3FF926BB0FECAFD3CFEB2" author="Forel, A." box="[151,738,260,282]" page="209" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" year="1902">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926BB0FECAFD3CFEB2" authority="Forel, 1902: 209" authorityName="Forel" authorityPageNumber="209" authorityYear="1902" box="[151,738,260,282]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Monomorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="gracillimum" variety="mayri">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926BB0FECAFE76FEB2" box="[151,424,260,282]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Monomorium gracillimum</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926AC2FECAFDFEFEB1" box="[485,544,260,281]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">mayri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF92690BFECAFD3CFEB2" author="Forel, A." box="[556,738,260,282]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="165 - 249" refId="ref7158" refString="Forel, A. (1902) Myrmicinae nouveaux de l'Inde et de Ceylan. Revue Suisse de Zoologie, 10, 165 - 249." type="journal article" year="1902">Forel, 1902: 209</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. Raised to species, senior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926FB7FECAFEFFFE90" authority="Wheeler" authorityName="Wheeler" authorityYear="1922" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Monomorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="karawajewi">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926FB7FECAFA42FEB2" box="[1168,1436,260,282]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Monomorium karawajewi</emphasis>
Wheeler
</taxonomicName>
: 
<treatmentCitation id="0ABD0D07FFC3FF926A0DFEECFE3AFE90" author="Bolton, B." box="[298,484,290,312]" page="326" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" year="1987">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926A0DFEECFE3AFE90" author="Bolton, B." box="[298,484,290,312]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="263 - 452" refId="ref6470" refString="Bolton, B. (1987) A review of the Solenopsis genus-group and revision of Afrotropical Monomorium Mayr (Hymenoptera: Formicidae). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Entomology, 54, 263 - 452." type="journal article" year="1987">
<collectingRegion id="49D8E5F4FFC3FF926A0DFEECFEAFFE90" box="[298,369,290,312]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bolton" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Bolton</collectingRegion>
, 1987: 326
</bibRefCitation>
</treatmentCitation>
.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C306789DFFC3FF926BB0FEA8FB2DFE42" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA32B16FFC3FF926BB0FEA8FB2DFE42" blockId="9.[151,1436,357,490]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926BB0FEA8FEA2FED5" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1902" box="[151,380,358,381]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Monomorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mayri">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926BB0FEA8FEA2FED5" box="[151,380,358,381]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Monomorium mayri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered one of the most common ant species of the Arabian Peninsula. It has been reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926A19FE47FE09FE0A" box="[318,471,393,418]" name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926AC2FE47FDF7FE0A" box="[485,553,393,418]" name="Oman" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Oman</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926941FE44FD6AFE09" box="[614,692,394,417]" name="Yemen" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Yemen</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF9269E2FE47FC7BFE0A" author="Collingwood, C. A." box="[709,933,393,418]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="230 - 302" refId="ref6815" refString="Collingwood, C. A. (1985) Hymenoptera: Fam. Formicidae of Saudi Arabia. Fauna Saudi Arabia, 7, 230 - 302." type="journal article" year="1985">Collingwood, 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926893FE47FAC4FE0A" author="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D." box="[948,1306,393,418]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="300 - 385" refId="ref6843" refString="Collingwood, C. A. &amp; Agosti, D. (1996) Formicidae of Saudi Arabia (Part 2). Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 15, 300 - 385." type="journal article" year="1996">Collingwood and Agosti, 1996</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<collectingCountry id="F30B6B86FFC3FF926E45FE47FA42FE0A" box="[1378,1436,393,418]" name="United Arab Emirates" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">UAE</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D56E7FFC3FF926BB9FE63FDDDFE6E" author="Tigar, B. J. &amp; Collingwood, C. A." box="[158,515,429,454]" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" pagination="13 - 14" refId="ref9012" refString="Tigar, B. J. &amp; Collingwood, C. A. (1993) A preliminary list of ant records from Abu Dhabi Emirate, UAE. Tribulus, 3, 13 - 14." type="journal article" year="1993">Tigar and Collingwood, 1993</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C5095FFC3FF926939FE60FCDBFE6D" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1902" box="[542,773,430,453]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Monomorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mayri">
<emphasis id="B968F704FFC3FF926939FE60FCDBFE6D" box="[542,773,430,453]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="574">Monomorium mayri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a common species at Rawdhat Khorim, exhibits high abundances from April to October, peaking in June and slowly declining from November to March.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
